<ui:composition xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
	xmlns:ui="http://java.sun.com/jsf/facelets"
	xmlns:f="http://java.sun.com/jsf/core"
	xmlns:h="http://java.sun.com/jsf/html"
	xmlns:rich="http://richfaces.org/rich"
	xmlns:a4j="http://richfaces.org/a4j"
	xmlns:jsflot="http://www.jsflot.org/taglib/jsflot">
	
<rich:panel id="firsttutPage" style="width: 100%;">
	<f:facet name="header">JSFlot Crosshair</f:facet>
	The crosshair is enabled via the crosshair attribute. When enabled the chart will display a crosshair instead of a mouse cursor. <br />
	<b>crosshair</b><br /> 
	Possible values are: <br />
	"x" : The crosshair is displayed along the X-axis<br />
	"y" : The crosshair is displayed along the Y-axis<br />
	"xy" : The crosshair is displayed along both axes. <br />
</rich:panel>

</ui:composition>